1	//! R6 — the interactive server's WEB rendering mode of theory content.
2	//!
3	//! The `main/message` and `main/rules` pane BODIES render the SAME blocks the
4	//! batch echo models, but: at width 100 / ribbon 67 (the default HughesPJ
5	//! `Style`, not the batch 110/73); HTML-entity-escaped; with keyword / operator
6	//! / comment tokens wrapped in `<span class="hl_…">`; and WITHOUT the batch
7	//! signature header comment. See workspace/BEHAVIOR.md "Web mode (R6)" for the
8	//! capture provenance of every rule below.
9	//!
10	//! ONE model, TWO render targets. The block-doc builders in `signature` /
11	//! `rule` / `formula` / `lemma` emit their styled glyphs through the [`hl_kw`] /
12	//! [`hl_op_char`] / [`hl_op_text`] / [`hl_comment`] / [`hl_wrap`] wrappers here.
13	//! In batch mode (the default) each wrapper is the identity — the R1–R5 output
14	//! is byte-for-byte unchanged. In web mode (inside [`html_render`]) each wraps
15	//! its glyph in a zero-width span-marker pair — mirroring the sanctioned
16	//! `Annotated.HughesPJ` `AnnotStart`/`AnnotEnd`: `sized_text(0, …)` sentinels
17	//! that flow through best/fits/lay at zero width, so the LAYOUT is identical to
18	//! the plain render. [`html_render`] then renders at (100, 67) and runs one pass
19	//! that entity-escapes the text and expands the sentinels into the spans.
20	
21	use std::cell::Cell;
22	
23	use crate::ast::{AcVariants, Restriction, Rule, Signature};
24	use crate::doc::{beside_op, char, render_with, sized_text, text, Doc};
25	use crate::{formula, lemma, rule, signature};
