1	//! R6 acceptance — the web rendering mode of theory content.
2	//!
3	//! For every captured `main/message` / `main/rules` pane across the corpus, this
4	//! sweep decodes the response envelope, inverts the producers-clean skin
5	//! (un-postprocess → logical lines → headed blocks), reconstructs each section's
6	//! MODEL from its body (spans stripped, entities unescaped, parsed
7	//! layout-insensitively), RE-RENDERS it through the web-mode path, and asserts
8	//! byte-identity of every section body — so the layout (width 100 / ribbon 67),
9	//! the `hl_*` span injection and the entity escaping are all re-derived, not
10	//! copied through. It also reassembles the whole pane through a faithful replica
11	//! of the producers skin and byte-compares the entire response envelope.
12	//!
13	//! Raw envelopes are materialized (scratchpad/r6/raw) from the sanctioned
14	//! capture corpus; point `R6_RAW` elsewhere to override.
15	
16	mod common;
